public class Main {

/*The printItems method accepts a single parameter, an integer n. The method will use the value of n to determine the number of items to be printed.*/
    public static void printItems(int n) {
/*The for loop starts with a counter, i, initalized at 0 and continues as long as i is less than n, and increments i by 1 with each iteration. Inside the look, the method prints the current value of i to the console followed by a new line.*/
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }

    /* The final result is a method that, when called with an argument n, prints the integer numbers from 0 to n-1 on separate lines. */
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        printItems(10);
    }
}
